                                        Linux Basics for DevOps
--> Linux is the backbone of DevOps and cloud computing.
AWS EC2, Docker containers, Kubernetes nodes, all run on Linux.

1. Linux Directory Structure
/
â”œâ”€â”€ bin     (binaries)
â”œâ”€â”€ etc     (configuration)
â”œâ”€â”€ home    (user home directories)
â”œâ”€â”€ usr     (apps & tools)
â”œâ”€â”€ var     (logs)
â”œâ”€â”€ tmp     (temporary files)
â””â”€â”€ root    (root user)

2. Important Linux Commands
ğŸ” Navigation
pwd      # show current directory
ls       # list files
cd       # change directory

ğŸ“ File Operations
cp file1 file2
mv old new
rm file
mkdir folder
touch file.txt

ğŸ“ƒ Viewing Files
cat file
head file
tail file
less file

ğŸ”§ Permissions
chmod 755 file
chown user:user file

ğŸ” System Info
